==English==
===Etymology===
From French '''[[dette]]''', from Latin '''[[debitum]]'''. A common English misspelling includes an unpronounced "b", which is an archaicism from the Latin "[[debitum]]". 

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/d&#603;t/}}

===Noun===
'''debt''' (''plural:'' '''[[debts]]''')
#something that is [[owe|owed]] to another
#something you are bound to perform or repay
#Money that one person or entity [[owe|owes]] or is required to pay to another, generally as a result of a loan or other [[monetary]] transaction.

